    Add RSS feed fetching system and intelligent article lifecycle management
    
    Backend - Article Fetching System:
    - Add RSS feed support to Source model (rss_feed_url, is_active, fetch_frequency)
    - Create fetch_articles management command with RSS feed parsing
    - Add add_sources command to populate 8 major tech news sources
    - Install feedparser, beautifulsoup4, python-dateutil for feed parsing
    - Add published_date field to Article model
    - Implement automatic category detection based on content keywords
    - Add fetch error tracking (last_fetch_status, last_fetch_error)
    - Support for TechCrunch, The Verge, Ars Technica, Wired, VentureBeat, Hacker News, MIT Tech Review, ZDNet
    
    Backend - Intelligent Article Lifecycle:
    - Add state field to Article model (fresh/active/archived)
    - Add archived_at timestamp for tracking archival
    - Implement automatic state transitions based on article age:
      * 0-7 days: fresh (new content, top priority)
      * 7-30 days: active (recent but not new)
      * 30+ days: archived (hidden from default feed)
    - Add database indexes for efficient state-based queries
    - Protect bookmarked articles from auto-archiving
    - Add helper methods: is_fresh(), is_archived(), age_in_days()
    - Create archive_old_articles management command with dry-run support
    - Update ArticleViewSet to exclude archived articles by default
    - Add smart feed prioritization (fresh → active → archived, then by date)
    - Add article_stats API endpoint for dashboard metrics
    
    Frontend - Enhanced Dashboard:
    - Make all dashboard stat cards clickable with navigation
    - Add Total Articles card linking to home page
    - Add fresh articles count indicator
    - Add Article Lifecycle info banner explaining states
    - Update dashboard to show article statistics
    - Improve card hover effects and visual feedback
    - Add navigation to filtered views (pending follow-ups, etc.)
    
    Admin:
    - Update Article admin to show state and archived_at fields
    - Add list filters for article state
    - Display fetch status in Source admin
    
    Features:
    - Automatic RSS article fetching from multiple sources
    - Smart feed that stays clean and relevant
    - Archived articles still searchable but hidden from main feed
    - Bookmark protection (bookmarked articles never archived)
    - Batch archive management with dry-run testing
    - Category auto-detection from article content
    - Source-based fetch frequency control
    - Dashboard article metrics and lifecycle explanation
    
    Commands:
    - python manage.py add_sources (populate news sources)
    - python manage.py fetch_articles (fetch from RSS feeds)
    - python manage.py fetch_articles --force (ignore frequency limits)
    - python manage.py archive_old_articles (auto-archive old articles)
    - python manage.py archive_old_articles --dry-run (preview archival)
    - python manage.py archive_old_articles --days 60 (custom threshold)

